00:35:49.530 --> 00:35:52.160
And all the ISPs said
hey, wait a minute,

00:35:52.160 --> 00:35:55.150
that's not going to work.

00:35:55.150 --> 00:35:57.200
So they passed this
Good Samaritan Provision

00:35:57.200 --> 00:35:59.117
which was trying to let
them get off the hook.

00:35:59.117 --> 00:36:01.366
It is actually a little bit
more complicated than that

00:36:01.366 --> 00:36:03.970
because this had to do with the
republicans and the democrats

00:36:03.970 --> 00:36:07.760
and stuff that got worked out
in committee and different bills

00:36:07.760 --> 00:36:10.560
of which pieces were taken from
other bills and put together.

00:36:10.560 --> 00:36:13.300
Winston Churchill
once said that anyone

00:36:13.300 --> 00:36:17.690
who likes sausages or law
should never watch either

00:36:17.690 --> 00:36:19.920
of them being made.

00:36:19.920 --> 00:36:24.610
And the Communications Decency
Act is a little bit like that.

00:36:27.940 --> 00:36:31.434
Well, the law got
passed in February 1996.

00:36:31.434 --> 00:36:33.350
The whole civil liberties
were all going nuts.

00:36:33.350 --> 00:36:37.330
Everybody who was looking
at Internet law went nuts.

00:36:37.330 --> 00:36:41.230
If you take 6.805
there is a long story

00:36:41.230 --> 00:36:45.250
