00:45:13.080 --> 00:45:18.140
How could it conceivably have
been the intent of congress,

00:45:18.140 --> 00:45:23.840
in a law that was motivated
by protecting kids

00:45:23.840 --> 00:45:26.040
from pornography
on the Internet.

00:45:26.040 --> 00:45:29.060
How could it conceivably been
the intent of congress

00:45:29.060 --> 00:45:30.900
that a consequence
of that law is now

00:45:30.900 --> 00:45:33.620
that somebody who is
trafficking in child pornography

00:45:33.620 --> 00:45:34.860
is actually immunized?

00:45:37.860 --> 00:45:41.740
But that is the current
state of the world.

00:45:41.749 --> 00:45:43.040
And you see what it comes from.

00:45:43.040 --> 00:45:46.140
It comes from looking at
this very complex system

00:45:46.140 --> 00:45:49.220
of regulations and the
interaction between First

00:45:49.220 --> 00:45:53.910
Amendment Law and
defamation law and the fact

00:45:53.910 --> 00:45:56.770
that you can apply regulations.

00:45:56.770 --> 00:45:59.400
You want to partly
immunize those ISPs,

00:45:59.400 --> 00:46:02.970
but you don't want
to let them off free.

00:46:02.970 --> 00:46:06.490
And you end up with
exactly the same kinds

00:46:06.490 --> 00:46:11.710
of unintended consequences
that happen whenever you

00:46:11.710 --> 00:46:13.120
monkey with any complex system.

00:46:13.120 --> 00:46:15.520
It is not a whole lot different
from the kind of stuff

00:46:15.520 --> 00:46:17.200
you have seen on
the technology side

00:46:17.200 --> 00:46:19.241
when you are talking about
how the technical base

00:46:19.241 --> 00:46:21.664
of the Internet works.

00:46:21.664 --> 00:46:22.830
So where does that leave us?

00:46:22.830 --> 00:46:28.450
Well, I guess in
terms of the law,

00:46:28.450 --> 00:46:35.610
it kind of leaves us there in
a very, very confused state.

00:46:35.610 --> 00:46:37.560
And getting more
and more confused

00:46:37.560 --> 00:46:39.660
because what has
happened recently,

00:46:39.660 --> 00:46:41.880
this whole thing is now
mixed in international law.

